# Pure Java Migration - CreateClaim Procedure

Analyzing the RPG procedure `CreateClaim`, I will generate a complete Pure Java application with layered architecture. This procedure processes claim position data from HSGPSLF3, aggregates it by failure number, and creates claim failures in HSG73PF.

## Analysis Summary
- **Purpose**: Create claim failures from position data (HSGPSLF3), aggregating material/labor/special values by failure number
- **Key Logic**: 
  - Read HSGPSLF3 by key (KEY_GPS)
  - Group positions by failure number (GPS150)
  - Identify maintenance work (ARB with 'WARTUNG' in text)
  - Extract main/subgroup from labor positions
  - Find highest-value material part
  - Aggregate values by type (MAT/ARB/other)
  - Create failure records via createFail() procedure
  - Update claim status to 3 if found
- **Files**: HSGPSLF3 (positions), HSG71PF (claim header), HSG73PF (claim failures)
- **SQL**: One EXEC SQL for uppercase conversion

